docs.abstract: Activities to help students learn about a significant moment in L.G.B.T.Q. history using contemporary articles, videos, photographs and The Times’s archive.
docs.snippet: Activities to help students learn about a significant moment in L.G.B.T.Q. history using contemporary articles, videos, photographs and The Times’s archive.
docs.lead_paragraph: Next month is the 52nd anniversary of the Stonewall uprising. On June 28, 1969, police officers raided the Stonewall Inn, a gay bar in New York City, with the stated purpose of reprimanding unlicensed bars that were illegally selling alcohol. Police raids on gay bars at the time were routine; the raid on that evening in 1969, however, incited a protest that galvanized the modern gay rights movement.

headline.main: Six Ways to Learn About Stonewall Using The New York Times
